8 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
9 Section 1. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 10-120 is hereby amended to read as
10 follows: 10-120. (a) Whenever an election is required for the issuance of
11 bonds for any purpose by any municipality other than an irrigation
12 district or where a different procedure for giving notice of the election is
13 specifically provided by law, upon compliance with the legal
14 requirements necessary and precedent to the call for the election, the
15 proper municipal officers shall call an election. The election shall be
16 held within 60 days after compliance with the necessary requirements, or
17 within 90 days, should the longer period include the date of a general
18 election on the date of a general election, primary election or special
19 election, as such terms are defined in K.S.A. 25-2502, and amendments
20 thereto.
21 (b) Notice of the election shall be published in a newspaper of
22 general circulation in the municipality once each week for two
23 consecutive weeks. The first publication shall be not less than 21 days
24 prior to the election. Notice of the election shall also be published on the
25 website of the county election office of any county where the election is
26 to be conducted. Such notice shall be published not less than 21 days
27 prior to the election and shall remain on the website until the day after
28 the election. The notice shall set forth the time and place of holding the
29 election and the purpose for which the bonds are to be issued and shall
30 be signed by the county election officer. The election shall be held at the
31 usual place of holding elections and shall be conducted by the officers or
32 persons provided by law for holding elections in the municipality.
33 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 25-1115 is hereby amended to read as
34 follows: 25-1115. (a) "General election" means the elections held on the
35 Tuesday following the first Monday in November of both even-numbered

