1 and odd-numbered years, and in the case of an election of any officers to
2 fill vacancies held on a date other than the Tuesday following the first
3 Monday in November, the election at which any such officer is finally
4 elected.
5 (b) "Primary election" means the elections held on the first
6 Tuesday in August of both even-numbered and odd-numbered years and
7 any other preliminary election held on a date other than the first
8 Tuesday in August at which part of the candidates for election to any
9 national, state, county, city, school or other municipal office are
10 eliminated by the process of the election but at which no officer is finally
11 elected.
12 (c) "Special election" means any election that is not a general or
13 primary election, including, but not limited to, any mail ballot election
14 conducted pursuant to K.S.A. 25-431 et seq., and amendments thereto. A
15 special election shall not be held within 45 days of a general or primary
16 election but may be held on the same day as a general or primary election
17 held on the first Tuesday after the first Monday in April of any year or on
18 the same day as a general or primary election.
19 Sec. 3. K.S.A. 25-2006 is hereby amended to read as follows: 25-
20 2006. As used in article 20 of chapter 25 of the Kansas Statutes Annotated,
21 and amendments thereto:
22 (a) "General election" means the election held for school officers
23 on the Tuesday following the first Monday in November of odd-
24 numbered years, and in the case of special elections of any school
25 officers to fill vacancies, the election at which any such officer is finally
26 elected.
27 (b) "Primary election" means the election held on the first Tuesday
28 in August of each odd-numbered year, and any other preliminary
29 election at which part of the candidates for special election to any school
30 office are eliminated by the process of the election but at which no
31 officer is finally elected.
32 (c) "Special election" means any election held on the first Tuesday
33 after the first Monday in April of any year or on the same day as a general
34 or primary election.
35 Sec. 4. K.S.A. 25-2019 is hereby amended to read as follows: 25-
36 2019. (a) No school district shall call or hold more than one special bond
37 election at a time other than on the same date as a primary or general
38 election, at a special election or the election of board of education
39 members within any one calendar year; nor shall any special bond
40 election be held within sixty (60) days before or after a general election or
41 election of members of the board of education of such district. The
42 provisions of this act shall not prohibit the planning for or consideration
43 of any bond election during the period between authorized bond

